Section 1:
1 L.D. 1760
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 EDUCATION AND CULTURAL AFFAIRS
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1178, L.D. 1760, “An Act to Promote
10 Public Education in Maine by Amending the Laws Governing Student Transfers”
11 Amend the bill in section 5 in subsection 6 in paragraph C-1 in the first line (page 3,
12 line 7 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "monthly" and inserting the following: 'yearly'
13 Amend the bill in section 5 in subsection 6 in paragraph C-1 in the 4th line (page 3,
14 line 10 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "the first day of each month" and inserting
15 the following: 'August 1st of each year'
16 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
17 number to read consecutively.
18 SUMMARY
1199 This amendment changes the requirement in the bill that a school administrative unit
2200 determine the available capacity by grade level in each of its schools from monthly to
2211 yearly and changes the posting requirement from the first day of each month to August 1st
2222 of each year.
2233 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2244 (See attached)
Page 1 - 132LR1349(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
